death.attack.bradberryBush: %1$s was poked to death by a Bradberry bush
death.attack.redcurrant: %1$s was poked to death by a Redcurrant bush
jitl.sen.knowledge_0: Ill trade you Overworld knowledge to get in there
jitl.sen.knowledge_1: See me when you have at least 75 Overworld Knowledge
jitl.sen.unlocked: I locked it for a reason but goodluck...
scroll.jitl.fail: Can't retrieve entry from scroll, report in Discord (unless this item came from creative tab)
scroll.jitl.sentry_gospel: We never saw it, but we know it - the Divine land Corba was birthed by the o' powerful Rock and Eye. Never forget the day, the hour, the second he - The True One - the all powerful Rock and Eye - cometh unto the great world he created, to seek his revenge on the wrong-doers who dare disrespect his land.
scroll.jitl.chap1.my_last_words: I have to make this quick Clancy... I'm not sure how much time I have left... I'm not sure how much time our reality has left. These horrid machines... they're evil. They've pioneered an art form of killing. These Sentries... I'm certain they will destroy reality as we know it if they become too powerful. They - I think they've found me... I hope this reaches you. Please take all of the other contents of my Ender Chest I've left you. They're yours now. Goodbye, my friend.
book.jitl.landing_text: Welcome $(playername) to Journey Into The Light, any other info needed head over to the $(l:https://discord.com/invite/WhXvz5b)Discord
book.jitl.category.getting_started.desc: This should give you the tips and hints on getting started.
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.iridium_: Ore that generates in the Overworld between Y -80 and 48, drops Iridium Nugget
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.sapphire: Ore that generates in the Overworld between Y -80 and 48, drops Sapphire Gem
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.shadium_: Ore that generates in the Overworld between Y -80 and 48, drops Raw Shadium
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.lunium_o: Ore that generates in the Overworld between Y -80 and 48, drops Lunium Powder
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.verdite_: Ore that generates in the Overworld between Y -80 and 48, drops itself
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.blood_ro: Stone that generates in the Nether between Y -64 and 256. This is used for Summoning Blocks and the Summoning Shrine
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.bloodcru: Ore that generates in the Nether Y -64 and 256, drops Raw Bloodcrust
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.bleedsto: Ore that generates in the Nether on the roof, drops Bleedstone Gem
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.smithsto: Ore that generates in the Nether on the roof, drops Smithstone Gem
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.warped_q: Ore that generates in the Nether Biome Warped Forest, drops Warped Quartz
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.crimson_: Ore that generates in the Nether Biome Crimson Forest, drops Crimson Quartz
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.fireston: Ore that generates in the Nether in Basalt, drops Firestone
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.enderill: Ore that generates in the End Islands, drops Enderillium Shard
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.ashual_o: Ore that generates in the Boiling Point, drops Ash
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.blazium_: Ore that generates in the Boiling Point, drops Raw Blazium
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.mekyum_o: Ore that generates in Euca Biome Goldite Grains, drops Mekyum Gem
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.celestiu: Ore that generates in Euca Biome Euca Plains, drops Celestium Gem
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.storon_o: Ore that generates in Euca Biome Goldite Grains, drops Storon Gem
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.korite_o: Ore that generates in Euca Biome Euca Plains, drops Korite Gem
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.rimeston: Ore that generates in Frozen Lands, drops Rimestone
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.peridot_: Ore that generates in Frozen Lands, drops Peridot Gem
Ore that generates in The Depths, drops itself
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.flairium: Ore that generates in The Depths, drops itself
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.orbadite: Ore that generates in Corba, drops Raw Orbadite
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.gorbite_: Ore that generates in Corba, drops Gorbite Gem
book.jitl.entry.getting_started.lunite_o: Ore that generates in Cloudia, drops Lunite Chunk
book.jitl.entry.portals.boil: You find the Portal Frame blocks inside the $(l:jitl:structures/boil_lock_structure)Boil Lock structure
book.jitl.entry.portals.frozen: You can craft the Frozen Portal Frame blocks to gain access
book.jitl.entry.portals.euca: You can craft the Euca Portal Frame blocks with Euca Portal Pieces dropped by Nether Bosses ($(l:jitl:nether/bosses#okoloo)Okoloo$(/l), $(l:jitl:nether/bosses#withering_beast)Withering Beast$(/l), $(l:jitl:nether/bosses#soul_watcher)Soul Watcher$(/l))
book.jitl.entry.portals.depths: You can craft the Depths Portal Frame blocks with Depths Portal Pieces dropped by Euca Bosses ($(l:jitl:euca/bosses#eudor)Eudor$(/l), $(l:jitl:euca/bosses#corallator$)Corallator$(/l))
book.jitl.entry.portals.corba: You can craft the Corba Portal Frame blocks with Corba Portal Pieces dropped by Depths Bosses ($(l:jitl:depths/bosses#scale)Scale$(/l), $(l:jitl:depths/bosses#thunder_bird)Thunder Bird$(/l))
book.jitl.entry.portals.terrania: You can craft the Terranian Portal Frame blocks with Terrania Portal Pieces dropped by Corba Bosses ($(l:jitl:corba/bosses#logger)Logger$(/l), $(l:jitl:corba/bosses#sentry_king)Sentry King$(/l))
book.jitl.entry.portals.cloudia: You can craft the Cloudia Portal Frame blocks with Cloudia Portal Pieces dropped by a Terrania Boss ($(l:jitl:terrania/bosses#terranian_protector)Terranian Protector$(/l))
book.jitl.category.summoning.desc: Information needed on creating the Summoning Shrine
book.jitl.entry.summoning.book.desc: Craft the book needed to find the recipes to summon all the JITL bosses
book.jitl.category.overworld.desc: Information on added features to the Overworld
book.jitl.category.nether.desc: Information on added features to the Nether
book.jitl.category.end.desc: Information on added features to The End
book.jitl.category.boil.desc: Information on features in the Boiling Point
book.jitl.category.frozen.desc: Information on features in the Frozen Lands
book.jitl.category.depths.desc: Information on features in The Depths
book.jitl.entry.overworld.tower_structur: Found randomly in any Overworld Biomes, climb your way to the top to find $(l:jitl:overworld/bosses#tower_guardian)Tower Guardian$(/l), Kill him if you can and open his Boss Crystal to receive keys to unlock the loot chests
book.jitl.entry.overworld.tower_guardian: Tower Guardian is one of the starting bosses, he has 275 Health and 5 Attack Damage, he can smash down on you which occasionally causes an explosion.
book.jitl.entry.overworld.rockite_dungeo: Found randomly in any Overworld Biomes underground between -Y32 and -Y56, Break the stone Rockite Smasher with any Pickaxe to spawn in the $(l:jitl:overworld/bosses#rockite_smasher)Rockite Smasher$(/l) boss, Kill him if you can and open his Boss Crystal to receive keys to unlock the loot chests
book.jitl.entry.overworld.rockite_smashe: Rockite Smasher is one of the starting bosses, he can only be damaged with any Pickaxe. He has 175 Health and 10 Attack Damage, he can throw you up to damage you.
book.jitl.entry.overworld.ancient_struct: The Ancient Structure holds the Portal for Senterian, you can open this up by going to the top of the structure and
filling each corner with an Ancient piece (shard or chunk as well) and clicking the middle block with an Ancient Eye of Opening
Inside the bottom you will find $(l:jitl:overworld/traders#neutral_sentry_stalker)Neutral Sentry Stalker$(/l) wanting information on the overworld
Once you give him information he will drop the key he used to lock the room, open it up and fill the missing spots with Sentry Eyes
book.jitl.entry.overworld.mage_hut.desc: Found randomly in any Dark Forest Biome, Climb up the top to find and meet the $(l:jitl:overworld/traders#mage)Mage
book.jitl.entry.overworld.blacksmith_hou: Found randomly in any Plains, Meadow, Sunflower Plains, Forest, Flower Forest, Birch Forest and Cherry Grove Biomes, Climb up the top to find and meet the $(l:jitl:overworld/traders#blacksmith)Blacksmith
book.jitl.entry.overworld.gunsmith_house: Found randomly in any Plains, Meadow, Sunflower Plains, Forest, Flower Forest, Birch Forest and Cherry Grove Biomes, Climb up the top to find and meet the $(l:jitl:overworld/traders#gunsmith)Gunsmith
book.jitl.entry.nether.boil_lock.desc: Unbreakable structure which you need to unlock with a Boiling Lock Key which is found in the Nether Tower. This structure contains the Boiling Point Portal Frames
book.jitl.entry.nether.nether_tower.desc: Loot Tower which has locked chests (unlocked with a crafted Nether Chest Key) which may hold a Boiling Lock Key which is used on the Boil Lock structure, also contains Mini Ghast spawners and extra loot
book.jitl.entry.nether.hellbot.desc: Spawns Hellbots which drops items that is used to craft Nether Chest Keys
book.jitl.entry.nether.okoloo_crypt.desc: A structure that you place the Broken Okoloo Club into the Pedestal to spawn $(l:jitl:nether/bosses#okoloo)Okoloo
book.jitl.entry.overworld.mage.desc: Mage is a trading NPC that lives up the top of $(l:jitl:overworld/structures#mage_hut)Mage Hut
book.jitl.entry.overworld.blacksmith.des: Blacksmith is a trading NPC that lives up the top of $(l:jitl:overworld/structures#blacksmith_house)Blacksmith House
book.jitl.entry.overworld.neutral_sentry: This Sentry Stalker is a bit different to normal... He locked the Senterian Portal away trying to close it away while he finds enough information on the Overworld. While he resides inside of the $(l:jitl:overworld/structures#ancient_tower)Ancient Tower$(/l) he will give the key inside for an exchange
Rockite Golem is a trading NPC and spawns underground randomly
book.jitl.entry.nether.blazier.desc: Blazier is spawned using the Blazier Orb made inside the Summoning Table, he has 850 Health, when he gets below 50% health he spawns help
book.jitl.entry.nether.calcia.desc: Calcia is spawned using the Calcia Orb made inside the Summoning Table, he has 650 Health, he likes to choose when he is seen...
book.jitl.entry.nether.okoloo.desc: Okoloo is spawned inside the $(l:jitl:nether/structures#okoloo_crypt)Okoloo Crypt$(/l), he has 600 Health, he likes to swing his club
book.jitl.entry.nether.soul_watcher.desc: The Soul Watcher is spawned using the Soul Watcher Orb made inside the Summoning Table, he has 650 Health, make sure to contain him or he may fly away
book.jitl.entry.nether.withering_beast.d: Withering Beast is spawned using the Withering Beast Orb made inside the Summoning Table, he has 750 Health, deadly to the touch.
book.jitl.entry.terrania.terranian_prote: Terranian Protector is spawned using the Enchanted Terrastar made inside the Summoning Table, he has 2500 Health it shoots heavy Mud which does 7.5x Hearts of damage per impact
book.jitl.entry.boil.brison.desc: The Brison is found in the Charred Fields Biome and keeps the $(l:jitl:boil/traders#escaped_convict)Escaped Convict$(/l) with a few needed spawners attached
book.jitl.entry.boil.mobs.escaped_convic: Escaped Convict is a NPC that lives in the $(l:jitl:boil/structures#brison)Brison
book.jitl.entry.boil.hellwing_tower.desc: The Hellwing Tower is found inside the Boiling Sands Biome and spawns $(l:jitl:boil/mobs#hellwing)Hellwings$(/l)
book.jitl.entry.boil.observer_hut.desc: The Observer Hut is found inside the Boiling Biome and spawns $(l:jitl:boil/mobs#observer)Observers$(/l)
book.jitl.entry.frozen.mobs.eskimo.desc: The Eskimo is a Trading NPC that lives in the $(l:jitl:frozen/structures#eskimo_camp)Eskimo Camp$(/l), He is the only way to get Frostborn Souls
book.jitl.entry.frozen.eskimo_camp.desc: The Eskimo Camp is found inside the Dying Forest Biome and spawns $(l:jitl:frozen/traders#eskimo)Eskimos$(/l)
book.jitl.entry.frozen.frozen_dungeon.de: The Frozen Dungeon is found in any Frozen Lands Biome and spawns $(l:jitl:frozen/mobs#frozen_frostbiter)Frozen Frostbiter$(/l)
book.jitl.entry.frozen.guardian_ruins.de: The Guardian Ruins is found inside the Dying Forest Biome and inside has 8 Pedestals and the $(l:jitl:frozen/traders#frozen_guardian)Frozen Guardian$(/l), place 8 x Frostborn souls (collected by trading with an $(l:jitl:frozen/traders#eskimo)Eskimos$(/l)) on the pedestals and interact with the Guardian, this will remove the storm from the dimension and complete the Frozen Knowledge system
book.jitl.entry.frozen.mobs.frozen_guard: The Frozen Guardian is a idle NPC that lives in the $(l:jitl:frozen/structures#guardian_ruins)Guardian Ruins$(/l), He just wants warmth and peace but his anger is the only thing standing between him leaving the Frozen Lands Dimension, without him the storm will be gone
book.jitl.entry.frozen.spike_dungeon.des: The Spike Dungeon is found the Frozen Wastes Biome and spawns $(l:jitl:frozen/bosses#frost_golem)Frost Golem$(/l)
book.jitl.entry.frozen.frost_golem.desc: Frost Golem is a Boss that lives in the $(l:jitl:frozen/structures#spike_dungeon)Spike Dungeon$(/l), he will hit you up into the air. He has 350 Health and 10 Damage
book.jitl.entry.boil.trader_hut.desc: The Trader Hut is found in the Scorched Wastelands Biome and keeps the $(l:jitl:boil/traders#boil_trader)Boil Trader$(/l)
book.jitl.entry.boil.mobs.boil_trader.de: Boil Trader is a NPC that lives in the $(l:jitl:boil/structures#trader_hut)Trader Hut
book.jitl.entry.euca.corallator.desc: The Corallator is spawned using the Corallator Orb made inside the Summoning Table, he has 950 Health, make sure to trap him or he might fly away
book.jitl.entry.euca.eudor.desc: Eudor is the Royal of the lands and is spawned using Eudor's Crown which the $(l:jitl:euca/traders#royal_king)Royal King$(/l) will give you, he has 950 Health, he sure is strong and is only seen when he wants to be
book.jitl.entry.euca.alloy_mender_hut.de: The Alloy Mender's Hut is found in the Goldite Grains Biome and resides the $(l:jitl:euca/traders#alloy_mender)Alloy Mender$(/l)
book.jitl.entry.euca.mobs.alloy_mender.d: Alloy Mender is a trader NPC that lives in his $(l:jitl:euca/structures#alloy_mender_hut)Hut$(/l), He moved away from the village to find his own riches
book.jitl.entry.euca.euca_palace.desc: Euca Palace is found in the Goldite Grains Biome and resides the $(l:jitl:euca/traders#royal_king)Royal King$(/l)
book.jitl.entry.euca.mobs.royal_king.des: The Royal King is the keeper of Eudor, he is a idle NPC that lives in the $(l:jitl:euca/structures#euca_palace)Euca Palace$(/l), Once you put on the Royal Pedestals around him what the wants he will give you his Crown
book.jitl.entry.euca.euca_village.desc: Euca Village is found in the Goldite Plains Biome and resides some $(l:jitl:euca/traders#crypian)Crypians$(/l)
book.jitl.entry.euca.mobs.crypian.desc: Crypian is a possible trader NPC that lives in the $(l:jitl:euca/structures#euca_village)Euca Village$(/l), He is a Goldbot that found his Sprocket to go back to normal
book.jitl.entry.euca.euca_sphere.desc: Euca Sphere is found in any Euca Biomes and spawns $(l:jitl:euca/mobs#goldbot)Goldbots$(/l), it also contains loot witch is unlockable with Euca Keys found in chests inside Euca
book.jitl.entry.euca.gold_bot_spawner.de: Goldbot Spawner is found in any Euca Biomes and spawns $(l:jitl:euca/mobs#goldbot)Goldbots$(/l)
book.jitl.entry.depths.dark_sorcerers_du: Dark Sorcerers Dungeon spawns $(l:jitl:depths/mobs#dark_sorcerer)Dark Sorcerers$(/l) when inside, it is unlocked with Depths Lock Key obtained from $(l:jitl:depths/traders#staring_guardian)Staring Guardian$(/l)
book.jitl.entry.depths.depths_watchtower: Depths Watchtower resides $(l:jitl:depths/traders#staring_guardian)Staring Guardian$(/l) up the top
book.jitl.entry.depths.mobs.staring_guar: Staring Guardian is a trading NPC that lives on top of the $(l:jitl:depths/structures#depths_watchtower)Depths Watchtower$(/l)
book.jitl.entry.depths.depths_village.de: Depths Village resides $(l:jitl:depths/traders#auron)Auron$(/l) and also new crops
book.jitl.entry.depths.mobs.auron.desc: Auron is a trading NPC that lives in the $(l:jitl:depths/structures#depths_village)Depths Village$(/l)
book.jitl.entry.depths.scale.desc: Scale is spawned using the Scale Orb made inside the Summoning Table, he has 1550 Health, make sure to trap him or he might fly away
book.jitl.entry.depths.thunder_bird.desc: Thunder Bird is spawned using the Thunder Bird Orb made inside the Summoning Table, he has 1550 Health, he has a hard hit with 10 Damage
book.jitl.entry.corba.corba_village.desc: Corba Village resides Trading NPC's and also new crops
book.jitl.entry.corba.seer_tree.desc: Seer Tree spawns $(l:jitl:corba/mobs#overseer)Overseers$(/l), once you have obtained an Elder Key from $(l:jitl:corba/traders#hooded)The Hooded$(/l) climb your way to the very top to spawn $(l:jitl:corba/mobs#overseer_elder)Overseer Elder$(/l)
book.jitl.entry.corba.mobs.green_tordo.d: Green Tordo is a trading NPC that lives in the $(l:jitl:corba/structures#corba_village)Corba Village$(/l)
book.jitl.entry.corba.mobs.hooded.desc: The Hooded is a trading NPC that lives in the $(l:jitl:corba/structures#corba_village)Corba Village$(/l)
book.jitl.entry.corba.mobs.red_tordo.des: Red Tordo is a trading NPC that lives in the $(l:jitl:corba/structures#corba_village)Corba Village$(/l)
book.jitl.entry.corba.mobs.overgrown_mer: Overgrown Merchant is a trading NPC that lives in the $(l:jitl:corba/structures#corba_village)Corba Village$(/l)
book.jitl.entry.corba.logger.desc: Logger is spawned using the Logger Orb made inside the Summoning Table, he has 2350 Health, he will throw you while he has a hard hit with 10 Damage
book.jitl.entry.corba.sentry_king.desc: Sentry King is spawned using the Sentry King Orb made inside the Summoning Table, he has 2500 Health, he will throw mud at you that hits hard with 15 Damage, his loot contains Ancient Eye of Opening which is used on the $(l:jitl:overworld/structures#ancient)Ancient Tower$(/l)
book.jitl.entry.terrania.mega_mushroom.d: Mega Mushroom is found in the Mushroom Biome and has 2 variants, each variant being Purple or Blue topped containing a different Trading NPC
book.jitl.entry.terrania.mega_tree.desc: Mega Tree is found in the Forest Biome and contains the Earthen Crystals which is needed to progress for making the Enchanted Terrastar in the Summoning Shrine
book.jitl.entry.terrania.mobs.terranian_: Terranian Enchanter is a trading NPC that lives in one variant of the $(l:jitl:terrania/structures#mega_mushroom)Mega Mushroom$(/l), he also trade the shards needed to get into the $(l:jitl:overworld/structures#ancient_structure)Ancient Structure$(/l)

Terranian Trader is a trading NPC that lives in one variant of the $(l:jitl:terrania/structures#mega_mushroom)Mega Mushroom$(/l), he also trade the shards needed to get into the $(l:jitl:overworld/structures#ancient_structure)Ancient Structure$(/l)
book.jitl.entry.cloudia.sky_stalker.desc: Sky Stalker is spawned using the Mysterious Disk which is traded to get from $(l:jitl:cloudia/traders#starlight_villager)Starlight Villager$(/l), be sure to trap him as he has 3500 Health and may fly away
book.jitl.entry.cloudia.mobs.starlight_v: Starlight Villager is a trading NPC that lives in one variant of the $(l:jitl:terrania/structures#cloudia_village_1)Cloudia Villages$(/l), he trades what you need for the Mysterious Disk to spawn $(l:jitl:cloudia/bosses#sky_stalker)Sky Stalker$(/l)
book.jitl.entry.cloudia.mobs.starlight_b: Starlight Blacksmith is a trading NPC that lives in one variant of the $(l:jitl:terrania/structures#cloudia_village_1)Cloudia Villages$(/l)
book.jitl.entry.senterian.senterian_alta: Senterian Altar Room is the biggest room in the dimension, in this room in the middle you will find the Senterian Altars, you can place a Sentry Observer item into them and they will spawn Mini Senterian Mobs, this is the only way to receive Sentacoins.
book.jitl.entry.overworld.mobs.brown_hon: Spawns in Forest like Biomes, Peaceful unless attacked, It has 40HP and does 4.25x Hearts of Damage, Chance to drop Hongoshrooms
book.jitl.entry.overworld.mobs.big_hongo: Spawns in Forest like Biomes, Peaceful unless attacked, It has 40HP and does 4.25x Hearts of Damage, Chance to drop Hongoshrooms
book.jitl.entry.overworld.mobs.medium_ho: Spawns in Forest like Biomes, Peaceful unless attacked, It has 30HP and does 2.5x Hearts of Damage, Chance to drop Hongoshrooms
book.jitl.entry.overworld.mobs.small_hon: Spawns in Forest like Biomes, Peaceful unless attacked, It has 20HP and does 1.5x Hearts of Damage, Chance to drop Hongoshrooms
Spawns in Snow like Biomes, Will attack on sight, It shoots Fireballs, It has 20HP, Chance to drop Snowballs
book.jitl.entry.overworld.mobs.boom_boom: Spawns in Overworld Biomes, Will attack on sight, Will create a medium explosion, It has 20HP, Chance to drop Gunpowder and TNT blocks
Spawns in Overworld Underground Biomes, Will attack on sight, It has 25HP and does 2.0x Hearts of Damage, Chance to drop Stone Clump, Cave Dust and Cave Crystal
book.jitl.entry.overworld.mobs.cavurn.de: Spawns in Overworld Underground Biomes, Will attack on sight, It has 30HP and does 2.0x Hearts of Damage, Chance to drop Cave Dust and Cave Crystal
book.jitl.entry.overworld.mobs.stonewalk: Spawns in Overworld Underground Biomes, Will attack on sight, It has 30HP and does 2.0x Hearts of Damage, Chance to drop Cave Dust, Stone Clump, Shadium Ingot, Lunium Ingot, Sapphire and Cave Crystal
book.jitl.entry.overworld.mobs.floro.des: Spawns in Forest like Biomes, Will attack on sight, Once not hiding away it will shoot projectiles, It has 25HP, Chance to drop Floro Pedal and Floro Seeds
book.jitl.entry.overworld.mobs.illager_m: Spawns in Illager Bunker, Peaceful unless attacked, It has 100HP and does 4.0x Hearts of Damage
book.jitl.entry.overworld.mobs.jungle_tu: Spawns in Jungle like Biomes, Peaceful unless attacked, It has 30HP and does 2.0x Hearts of Damage
book.jitl.entry.overworld.mobs.sand_craw: Spawns in Desert like Biomes, Will attack on sight, It has 20HP and does 2.0x Hearts of Damage, Chance to drop Sand Blocks
book.jitl.entry.overworld.mobs.spyclopse: Spawns in Desert like Biomes, Will attack on sight, It has 30HP and does 1.5x Hearts of Damage, Chance to drop Spyclopse Eye
book.jitl.entry.overworld.mobs.rockite_g: Spawns in Overworld Underground Biomes, Harmless, NPC Mob, Will trade with you, It has 100HP
book.jitl.entry.overworld.mobs.neutral_s: Spawns in $(l:jitl:overworld/structures#ancient_structure)Ancient Structure$(/l), Peaceful unless attacked, NPC Mob, Will trade with you once you reach 75 Overworld Knowledge, Will trade Sentacoins for Breakable versions of Senterian Blocks (Decorational), It has 100HP
book.jitl.entry.overworld.mobs.mage.desc: Spawns in $(l:jitl:overworld/structures#mage_hut)Mage Hut$(/l), Peaceful unless attacked, NPC Mob, Will trade with you, It has 100HP
book.jitl.entry.overworld.mobs.blacksmit: Spawns in $(l:jitl:overworld/structures#blacksmith_house)Blacksmith House$(/l), Peaceful unless attacked, NPC Mob, Will trade with you, It has 100HP
Spawns in $(l:jitl:overworld/structures#gunsmith_house)Gunsmith House$(/l), Peaceful unless attacked, NPC Mob, Will trade with you, It has 100HP
book.jitl.entry.overworld.mobs.robot.des: Spawns in Any Overworld Biome Biomes, Harmless, Will attack on site, It has 20HP, Chance to drop Iron Ingot and Redstone Dust
book.jitl.entry.overworld.mobs.pet_robot: Obtained from the $(l:jitl:overworld/traders#mage)Mage$(/l), Peaceful unless attacked, Tamable with Already tamed when spawned, can be healed with Pet Food, It has 40HP and does 3.0x Hearts of Damage
book.jitl.entry.overworld.mobs.ferret.de: Spawns in Forest like Biomes, Peaceful unless attacked, Tamable with Pet Food, It has 20HP and does 2.5x Hearts of Damage
book.jitl.entry.nether.mobs.hellbot.desc: Spawns in $(l:jitl:nether/structures#hellbot)Hellbot Structure$(/l), Will attack on sight, It has 30HP and does 4.0x Hearts of Damage, Chance to drop Flaming Sprocket, Hell Shards and Flaming Spring

jitl.trader.boil_trader1: Boil Trader: It's not often that newcomers arrive here. Can you stand the heat?
jitl.trader.boil_trader2: Boil Trader: I'm an unusual collector, but I have the best deals of any realm!
jitl.trader.boil_trader3: Boil Trader: I can see that you're having a tough time getting around. An armor upgrade, perhaps?
jitl.trader.escaped_convict1: Escaped Convict: I'm an innocent man! I have no reason to be in this realm!
jitl.trader.escaped_convict2: Escaped Convict: Don't be threatened by me, strange thing!
jitl.trader.escaped_convict3: Escaped Convict: I managed to find some great loot on my way here. If you can help me out of here, I'll give back in return.
jitl.trader.staring_guardian1: Guardian: It sure is dark down here... I've always speculated about what's on the surface.
jitl.trader.staring_guardian2: Guardian: You don't look like any normal creature I've seen here before. We don't get a lot of travelers.
jitl.trader.staring_guardian3: Guardian: It's always too dark here to see. Hopefully, there'll be a journey to the light as some wish.
jitl.trader.alloy_mender1: Alloy Mender: It takes over a thousand degreese to melt this gold!
jitl.trader.alloy_mender2: Alloy Mender: My weapons have been melted and shaped into deadly perfection!
jitl.trader.alloy_mender3: Alloy Mender: It's a real struggle living here, when everything wants to kill you...
jitl.trader.alloy_mender4: Alloy Mender: Did they steal my other things at the village?
jitl.trader.crypian1: Crypian: Yeah I took some of it
jitl.trader.crypian2: Crypian: IT'S MINE.... Unless you want it?
jitl.trader.crypian3: Crypian: I might go see where he has moved to....
jitl.npc.crypian_alloy1: Crypian: Alloy Mender used to live here, but he moved into the royal lands
jitl.npc.crypian_alloy2: Crypian: Everyone has raided his house
jitl.npc.crypian_alloy3: Crypian: I'm sure you could possibly trade with some of them
jitl.npc.crypian1: Crypian: I missed out on the Alloy Menders gear
jitl.npc.crypian2: Crypian: A few others have some of the Alloy Menders things
jitl.trader.eskimo1: Eskimo: Did you know its not as cold as it has been?
jitl.trader.eskimo2: Eskimo: Storms have been raging since the shrine showed up...
jitl.trader.eskimo3: Eskimo: Please sort out the shrine... It's Freezing!
jitl.trader.mage1: Mage: I have some great deals!
jitl.trader.mage2: Mage: I've got some nice valuables!
